 Because a time series of input prices was not 
 available, relative input and output prices are assumed to remain constant. Farmer's cost in supplying work hard to clean common narrow waterways and water fees 
 paid to WUAs are included as production costs, 
 because they account only for the cost of water 
 delivery (WUAs are non-profit organizations, and 
 they decide/figure out their own fees obeying 
 their capital and operating costs). The cost of labor 
