 2.4. (money-related) analysis of money-based rents to buyers 
 and sellers 
 (money-related) prices were employed in the crop budgets used in the analysis of individual money-based 
 rents to buyers and sellers. In this analysis, a wateruse right that was not used by the seller before the 
 transaction was valued at zero. The seller's net rent 
 is the sale price, (changed to make better/changed to fit new conditions) to 1993 values using 
 Chile's personal price index, less both the value of 
 the water to the seller and the seller's transactions 
 cost, as shown in Eq. (3): 
