 Of the shares sold in this valley, 90% had not 
 been used by their sellers over the last few years. Some of 
 these sellers had extra water, others had rights to 
 water along narrow waterways that did not conduct water (in a way that produces a lot with very little waste), others had quit farming, and sti11 other sellers owned rights to water but did not own land. In 
 general water that is not used by its owner is used by 
 close-by farmers in the same narrow waterway or section of 
 the river. 
